messages.message: On a deployment run, I'm seeing a incorrect extraction for the full name of the ID card holder. Could we take a look at this? This (https://aihub.instabase.com/review/7913edd8-ff3e-48f3-840c-32caba067dde?deploymentId=019712e6-7175-7288-b537-0cb2751201e7) is the deployment run and it's in the Instabase org

LOL, the text layer contains some text: “DUCDUC         LU”, almost like a hallucination. It would kinda make sense more as a name than the boilerplate “happy traveler”, so I would follow the LLM’s reasoning here.
There seems to be some hidden text that gets generated. Gemini does not find anything here, so maybe some OCR hallucination due to the vertical text? cc: @Anil
for some reason it gets USA USA as DUC DUC
This does show a flow with layout algorithm where department of state text got merged in with given name/sex
